CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 17, 1938, pg. 4, reads: "Mr. Joe Louis Meets Master Joe Louis - Heavyweight Champion Joe Louis had the pleasure of meeting his namesake in Pittsburgh last week while appearing here with his softball team... Here is big Joe Louis holding little Joe Louis of Pittsburgh. Looks like little Joe has a better deadpan expression than the champion, doesn't it?"
TitMainTitle: Boxer Joe Louis holding baby cousin Joe Louis Barrow, with Joe Louis Bombers softball teammates on Greenlee Field, and Frank Bolden and others in grandstand, Hill District
